    "ci_attrs": "<a href=\"#\" data-action=\"search-by-attr\" data-crit-field=\"ci_attrs_VAR4\">DI: Area IV</a>",
    "description": "<p>A critical study of childhood as found in scripture and through major thinkers in the Christian tradition. We consider the changing constructions of childhood across time, in both church and society, toward exploring what theological meanings of human personhood find expression in the particular ways we view children and childhood. How does attention to the childhood of God reframe or enlarge our perspectives on the nature of the Divine? From practical theology\u2019s transformational perspective, we address several contemporary global justice issues involving children, such as child trafficking, children of war, child poverty, HIV/AIDS, and child abuse. And, drawing on the frameworks of several contemporary scholars of childhood and religion, we explore what it means to welcome children in the church and the world today, focusing on ministries with children in light of a theologically reimagined view of childhood. The course includes a focus on pastoral care with children and engaging children\u2019s literature in ministry with children and their families. Area IV.</p>",
